1. 飲茶  
廣東話：星期日早上，阿媽成班姊妹約咗去飲茶，一於叫晒蝦餃、燒賣同叉燒包。  
English: On Sunday morning, Mom and her friends arranged to go for yum cha, and they ordered shrimp dumplings, siu mai, and barbecue pork buns.

2. 圖書館  
廣東話：我成日放工之後去圖書館睇書，度安靜又涼快。  
English: I often go to the library to read books after work; it's quiet and cool there.

3. 養聲  
廣東話：佢唱K唱到聲沙，醫生話要返屋企養聲兩個禮拜。  
English: He sang karaoke until his voice got hoarse; the doctor said he needs to rest his voice for two weeks at home.

4. 票尾  
廣東話：入場之後記得保管好票尾，出閘要檢查㗎！  
English: Remember to keep your ticket stub after entering; they’ll check it when you exit!

5. hacker  
廣東話：呢個hacker黐線咗，竟然黐到政府系統度去。  
English: This hacker is crazy—he actually hacked into the government system.

6. 石斛蘭  
廣東話：我阿媽鍾意養石斛蘭，佢話呢種蘭花唔使成日淋水都得。  
English: My mom likes growing Dendrobium orchids; she says this kind of orchid doesn’t need watering all the time.

7. 吊詭（矛盾、悖論）  
廣東話：吊詭在於，你愈想放鬆，反而愈緊張。  
English: The paradox is, the more you try to relax, the more tense you become.

8. 吊詭（似非而是、荒謬）  
廣東話：佢話誠實係最大嘅謊話，呢句真係幾吊詭。  
English: He said honesty is the biggest lie—that statement is really paradoxical.

9. 各為其主  
廣東話：雖然佢哋以前係好拍檔，但而家各為其主，比賽入面都要全力對抗。  
English: Although they used to be good partners, now they work for different bosses and must compete fiercely in the game.

10. 軨蓋  
廣東話：車嘅軨蓋甩咗，啲沙泥飛入去搞到輪胎損耗得好快。  
English: The wheel cover fell off the car, and dirt got in, causing the tire to wear out quickly.

11. 打哥夫  
廣東話：週末我哋一班老友約咗去鄉村會所打哥夫，打完仲有燒烤。  
English: This weekend, we arranged to play golf at a country club, and there’ll be a barbecue after.

12. 免揀  
廣東話：呢間店賣嘅福袋全部免揀，買咗先至知入面有啲咩。  
English: All the lucky bags sold in this shop are non-selectable—you only know what’s inside after buying.

13. 擺闊佬  
廣東話：佢新開咗間公司，成日喺IG擺闊佬，成日post去高級餐廳食飯嘅相。  
English: He just started a new company and keeps showing off on Instagram, posting photos of dining at fancy restaurants.

14. 廣播劇  
廣東話：細個成日聽收音機聽廣播劇，聽到癮咗每晚準時收聽。  
English: As a kid, I often listened to radio dramas on the radio—I got addicted and tuned in every night.

15. 錄影機  
廣東話：我屋企部錄影機壞咗，唔知可唔可以執返。  
English: My videocamera broke down; I don’t know if it can be fixed.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩  
廣東話：證據擺喺度，你吟詩吟唔甩㗎喇，快啲承認啦！  
English: The evidence is right here—you can’t deny it anymore, just admit it quickly!

17. 佈道大會  
廣東話：禮拜日教會有佈道大會，牧師講得好有感染力。  
English: There’s a preaching event at church on Sunday; the pastor spoke very inspiringly.

18. 寫手（寫作的人）  
廣東話：佢做寫手做到出名，本本小說都賣到斷市。  
English: He became a famous writer—every one of his novels sells out.

19. 寫手（代筆）  
廣東話：佢唔識寫情書，唯有搵寫手代佢寫一封浪漫到爆嘅。  
English: He doesn’t know how to write love letters, so he hired a ghostwriter to write a super romantic one for him.

20. 代打  
廣東話：我今晚有事，你可唔可以幫我代打一局排位賽？  
English: I’m busy tonight—can you play a ranked match for me?

21. 茶碗  
廣東話：呢隻茶碗係日本製，手感好細膩，用嚟飲抹茶特別有feel。  
English: This tea bowl is Japanese-made, feels very smooth, and gives a special vibe when drinking matcha.

22. 茶隔  
廣東話：用茶隔好方便，斟茶嗰陣茶葉唔會落杯入面。  
English: Using a tea strainer is convenient—the tea leaves won’t fall into the cup when pouring.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈  
廣東話：老細成日遲到，但見到我遲五分鐘就鬧，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈！  
English: The boss is always late, but when I’m five minutes late, he yells at me—total double standard!

24. 獨唱  
廣東話：佢報咗獨唱項目，成場比賽都好緊張，但唱得幾好。  
English: He signed up for the solo singing event—was nervous the whole time, but sang really well.

25. 快人快事  
廣東話：佢真係快人快事，講完想買樓，三個禮拜內已經簽咗約。  
English: He’s such a decisive person—said he wanted to buy a house, and signed the contract within three weeks.

26. 四腳獸  
廣東話：聽講廁所有人做四腳獸，嚇親我以後都唔敢去隔籬間厠。  
English: I heard someone did “four-legged beast” in the toilet—I’m too scared to use that restroom now.

27. 無米粥  
廣東話：而家只係煲緊無米粥，成個計劃都未落實，唔好諗得太美好。  
English: Right now we’re just “cooking rice without rice”—the whole plan isn’t confirmed yet, so don’t get your hopes up.

28. 義會  
廣東話：我阿媽參加咗個義會，每月存一千，希望年底可以拎筆錢裝修。  
English: My mom joined a rotating savings group—she saves $1,000 each month, hoping to get a lump sum for renovation by year-end.

29. 榜文  
廣東話：古代科舉放榜嗰陣，榜文一貼出，成條街都擠滿人。  
English: In ancient times, when imperial exam results were posted, the notice board would be surrounded by crowds.

30. MK名  
廣東話：啲細路網上用MK名，成日見到「堅系CoolBoy☆」、「醉愛靚妹囡囡」咁樣。  
English: Kids use MK names online, like “GenuineCoolBoy☆” or “ObsessedWithPrettyGirlBaby.” [end of text]


